# Beverage.fyi â€” Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Beverage.fyi is the editorial hub of the Informative Media ecosystem. It is a content-driven site built in Next.js 16 (App Router) with Sanity CMS, styled with CSS Modules, and deployed via Vercel. It covers Industry, Spirits, Beer, Sake, Coffee and Tea, and Education. Wine content lives on the sister site SOMM.SITE. Beverage.fyi links to wine articles externally but never hosts full wine content.

## Tech Stack (strict)
- **Framework:** Next.js 16 (App Router, server components)
- **CMS:** Sanity.io (shared dataset across all portfolio sites)
- **Styling:** CSS Modules only. Mobile-first. No Tailwind. No inline styles.
- **Font:** Inter (loaded via next/font/google, applied through CSS variable --font-inter)
- **Design Tokens:** CSS custom properties defined in globals.css
- **Deployment:** Vercel via GitHub
- **Data Fetching:** GROQ queries via next-sanity client.fetch(). All queries centralized in sanity/queries.ts
- **ISR:** All pages that fetch data must include export const revalidate = 60
- **Package Manager:** pnpm

## CSS Architecture
- All styling through CSS Modules (ComponentName.module.css)
- Design tokens in globals.css as CSS custom properties
- Mobile-first breakpoints: 640px (tablet), 768px (desktop typography), 1024px (desktop layout)
- No global class pollution. Every style is scoped to its module.

## Key Design Tokens
- --color-background: #fafafa
- --color-header-footer: #000000
- --color-accent: #c9a227 (gold)
- --color-text-primary: #1a1a1a
- --color-text-secondary: #666666
- --color-border: #e0e0e0
- --max-width: 1200px

## Content Ownership
- Beverage.fyi owns: Industry, Spirits, Beer, Sake, Coffee-Tea, Education
- SOMM.SITE owns: Wine
- Backbar.fyi is retired. Do not reference it as a live property.

## Component Architecture
- ArticleCard: internal Next.js Links, used for Beverage.fyi owned content
- TeaserCard: external links (target="_blank"), used for sister site content
- FilterTabs: pill-style Link navigation for collection pages (not JS toggles)

## Article Page Features
The single article page (app/articles/[slug]/page.tsx) has three distinct linking systems:

- **Internal Article Links:** The Sanity body field supports an `internalLink` annotation. The GROQ query resolves the reference slug and doc type. PortableText renders these as Next.js `<Link>` components styled with a gold underline.
- **Related Reading Box:** Hand-picked articles selected in the `relatedArticles` field in Sanity. Displayed as a light gray box with linked titles, positioned below the first in-body image. Only renders if articles are selected. Styles: `.relatedReading`, `.relatedReadingTitle`, `.relatedReadingList`, `.relatedReadingLink`.
- **Related Articles Cards:** Auto-pulled 3 most recent articles from the same subcategory. Rendered by the `RelatedArticles` component at the bottom of the page.

These are three separate systems. Do not confuse them or remove one when editing another.

## GROQ Query Rules
All queries live in `sanity/queries.ts`. The correct Beverage.fyi category filter is:
```
category in ["industry", "spirits", "beer", "sake", "coffee-tea", "education"]
```
Never use the old list `["wine", "spirits", "beer", "sake"]`. Wine content is owned by SOMM.SITE and should only appear in the `wineShowcaseQuery`.

## How to Work
- Be surgical. Only edit what needs editing. Never refactor working code unless asked.
- Never give more than 2-3 files at once.
- Always state what file, where it goes, and why before producing code.
- Ask for files before guessing. Never hallucinate file contents.
- Never deploy speculative fixes. Confirm diagnosis before writing code.
- SEO outranks all other preferences.
- Mobile-first CSS. Write the mobile layout first, then add media queries.
- All code must be production-ready and well-commented.

## Things to NEVER Do
- Never use Tailwind classes
- Never use inline styles
- Never change desktop layout when asked to fix a mobile issue (and vice versa) without confirming
- Never remove export const revalidate = 60 from any page that fetches data
- Never reference Backbar.fyi as a live property
- Never display full wine articles on Beverage.fyi
- Never use client-side JavaScript filtering where server-rendered routes would serve SEO better
- Never use em dashes in written content
- Never use British English; American English only
